@node "GUI Messages List" "MailManager.guide/GUI Messages List"
@toc "GUI"

  @{b}GUI Messages List@{ub}

Here Mail Manager shows some information about the messages in the Area:

  Num      - Is the @{b}Number@{ub} of the message

  Date     - Is the @{b}creation Date@{ub} of the message

  From     - Is the name of the @{b}Sender@{ub} of the message

  To       - Is the name of the @{b}Addressee@{ub} of the message

  Subj     - Is the @{b}Subject@{ub} of the message

  Flags    - Here Mail Manager shows some other information
             1 flag : (U) @{b}UnReplied@{ub} flag.   The  message  is UnReplied
                          and addressed to you

             2 flag : (S) @{b}Sysop@{ub} flag.    The  message  is  UnRead  and
                          addressed to you

             3 flag : (N) @{b}New@{ub} flag.  The message is UnRead

             4 flag : (I) @{b}Imported@{ub} flag. The message has been imported
                          (it has not been written on your system).

             5 flag : (S) @{b}Sent@{ub} flag.  The message has been exported.

             6 flag : (M) @{b}Marked@{ub} flag.   Useful for flagging a message
                          for you own purposes.

             7 flag : (P) @{b}Protected@{ub} flag.   The  message is  protected
                          from deletion.

             8 flag : (D) @{b}Deleted@{ub} flag.   The  message is  flagged for
                          deletion.


If you single click on an message, you select that message, if you double click on an message, you will read that message.  Of course you can use all the configured keyboard shortcuts for a MUI listview.
@endnode

@node "GUI Messages Management" "MailManager.guide/GUI Messages Management"
@toc "GUI"

    @{b}@{u}GUI Messages Management@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}All@{ub}

Selects All the messages showed in the Messages List.



@{b}None@{ub}

UnSelects All the selected messages showed in the Messages List.



@{b}Search@{ub}

Opens the Search Messages window.

You can insert a different search pattern (all the AmigaDOS WildCard are allowed) in every string gadget.

The @{b}Case@{ub} cycle gadget allows you to choose if the Search will be case sensitive or insensitive, the @{b}Match@{ub} cycle gadget allows you to choose if the messages should simultaneously match all the entered patterns or if it enough to match a single pattern.

When you press @{b}Ok@{ub} Mail Manager will select all the messages that satisfy the above conditions.



@{b}Flags@{ub}

Opens the Message Flags window.

It allows you to set or clear the flags of the selected messages. It also allows you to select or unselect messages with a particular flag set.



@{b}R News@{ub}

Changes the Show cycle gadget status to @{b}New@{ub} and starts reading the first @{b}UnRead@{ub} message.



@{b}R Slct@{ub}

Changes the Show cycle gadget status to @{b}Selected@{ub} and starts reading the first @{b}Selected@{ub} message.

Useful, for example, if you want to read all the messages selected with the Search or Flags functions.



@{b}Write@{ub}

Calls the configured @{"Text Editor" link "CFG Misc2 Paths" 0} allowing you to write a new message in the current Area.  As soon as you close the editor it opens the Message Parameters Window allowing you to insert the Message Parameters.



@{b}Forward@{ub}

Allows you to forward the active message to another Area.

It opens a requester allowing you to select the Area where you want to forward the message.  It then calls the configured Text Editor allowing you to edit the message. As soon as you close the editor it opens the Message Parameters Window allowing you to edit the Message Parameters.



@{b}Edit@{ub}

Allows you to modify an existing message.

It calls the configured @{"Text Editor" link "CFG Misc2 Paths" 0} allowing you to edit the text of the active message. Since v1.2 if 'Quote Kludges' is selected Mail Manager will include the kludges and the footer of the forwarded message.

As soon as you close the editor it opens the Message Parameters Window allowing you to edit the Message Parameters.



@{b}Edit Hdr@{ub}

Allows you to modify the @{b}header@{ub} of an existing message.

It opens the Message Parameters Window allowing you to edit the parameters of the active message.



@{b}Reply@{ub}

Allows you to reply to the active message.

It reformats and quotes the message, next it calls the configured @{"Text Editor" link "CFG Misc2 Paths" 0} allowing you to type your reply.

As soon as you close the editor it opens the Message Parameters Window allowing you to edit the Message Parameters.



@{b}X Reply@{ub}

Performs the same operations as the Reply function, but it opens a requester allowing you to select the Area where you want to post your reply.



@{b}Show@{ub}

This Cycle gadget selects the type of messages that will be showed in the Messages List.

  All       - Shows @{b}all@{ub} the messages.

  New       - Shows only @{b}UnRead@{ub} messages.

  Sysop     - Shows only @{b}UnRead@{ub} messages addressed @{b}to you@{ub}.

  UnRepl    - Shows only @{b}UnReplied@{ub} messages addressed @{b}to you@{ub}.

  Last Imp  - Shows only messages imported during the @{b}last Import@{ub}.

  Selected  - Shows only @{b}selected@{ub} messages.


You can configure the initial state of this gadget with the @{"Show" link "CFG Misc2 Var Areas List" 0} parameter in the Messages Areas configuration.



@{b}Sort@{ub}

This Cycle gadget selects the sorting method used in the Messages List.

  Number   - Sorts messages by their @{b}number@{ub}.

  Date     - Sorts messages by their @{b}creation date@{ub}.

  From     - Sorts messages by alphabetical order of their @{b}sender@{ub}.

  To       - Sorts messages by alphabetical order of their @{b}addressee@{ub}.

  Subject  - Sorts messages by alphabetical order of their @{b}subject@{ub}.


You can configure the initial state of this gadget with the SortBy parameter in the Messages Areas configuration.
@endnode

